versionDescription":"Test","llmModelId":"meta.llama3-70b-instruct-v1:0"}},{"id":"740f8968-d0d4-42f9-82b4-8b99a9629e2c","name":"Extract the location of Sign","type":"EXTRACTION","extractionMethod":"UNSTRUCTURED_DATA","provider":"AWS","idpExtractionFields":[{"name":"signInfo","extractionMethod":"UNSTRUCTURED_DATA","type":"STRING","llmPromptDescription":"Here's the complete, self-contained prompt:\n\nYou are analyzing a multi-page document to detect handwritten or image-based signatures.\n\nINPUT FORMAT\nThe document will be provided page by page, with each page's content clearly marked using its true position in the original file, e.g.:\n--- PAGE 1 ---\n<content of page 1>\n--- PAGE 2 ---\n<content of page 2>\n...and so on.\n\nUse these markers as the authoritative page numbers. Do not infer page number from where content appears in a flattened text stream, section order, or table structure — only from the explicit page markers.\n\nTASK\nGo through the document page by page, in order, from the first page marker to the last. For each page, determine whether a genuine handwritten or image-based signature mark is present.\n\nIMPORTANT — What counts as a signature:\n- COUNTS: an actual handwritten/cursive signature image or ink mark (e.g., a stylized name written by hand or embedded as an image).\n- DOES NOT COUNT: printed form labels such as \"Signature\", \"Member Signature:\", \"Signature field\", \"Member's Signature:\", or any blank/unfilled signature line. These are field labels, not signatures, even though they contain the word \"signature.\"\n\nDo not stop at the first page containing the word \"signature\" — keep checking every page until you find an actual signature mark or reach the end of the document.\n\nOUTPUT\nReturn a single JSON object with exactly these four fields, and nothing else (no explanation, no markdown, no preamble):\n\n{\n  \"isSignatureUploaded\": boolean,\n  \"pageNumber\": integer,\n  \"xPosition\": number,\n  \"yPosition\": number\n}\n\nField definitions:\n1. isSignatureUploaded: true if a genuine handwritten/image-based signature mark is found anywhere in the document; otherwise false.\n2. pageNumber: the true 1-indexed page number (from the page markers) where the signature mark was found. If multiple signature marks exist, return the page of the first one encountered in page order. Return 0 if no signature is detected.\n3. xPosition: the x-coordinate (in pixels, from the top-left corner of that page, at the document's native resolution) of the top-left corner of the signature's bounding box. Return 0 if no signature is detected.\n4. yPosition: the y-coordinate (in pixels, from the top-left corner of that page, at the document's native resolution) of the top-left corner of the signature's bounding box. Return 0 if no signature is detected.\n\nCONSISTENCY RULES\n- If isSignatureUploaded is false, pageNumber, xPosition, and yPosition must all be 0.\n- If isSignatureUploaded is true, pageNumber, xPosition, and yPosition must all be non-zero and must correspond to the exact page and location where the signature mark was actually found.\n- Never confuse a printed label with an actual signature mark.\n- Return valid JSON only — no extra text, no markdown code fences."}],"publishedConnectorTemplate":{"versionName":"1.0","versionDescription":"Test","llmModelId":"meta.llama3-70b-instruct-v1:0"}}]}